Package: rcapstone
Title: Provides Access to NOAA Significant Earthquakes Database
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Niklaas", "Baudet von Gersdorff", email = "me@niklaas.eu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description:
    The package is developed as part of a Coursera capstone project on software
    development in R. It provides an API to the NOAA Significant Earthquakes
    Database (https://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/nndc/struts/form?t=101650&s=1&d=1)
    including processing and visualising the data.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.2)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Imports: 
    assertthat,
    dplyr,
    fs,
    grid,
    ggplot2,
    magrittr
